duck: concept definition: something conceived in the mind.
Concept learning - Concept learning, also known as category learning, concept attainment, and concept formation, is largely based on the works of the cognitive psychologist Jerome Bruner.
Abstraction - Abstraction is a process by which concepts are derived from the usage and classification of literal ("real" or "concrete") concepts, first principles, or other methods.
Class (philosophy) - Philosophers sometimes distinguish classes from types and kinds.
Concept map - A concept map is a diagram showing the relationships among concepts.
In metaphysics, and especially ontology, a concept is a fundamental category of existence.
Categorization - Categorization is the process in which ideas and objects are recognized, differentiated, and understood.
Concept and object - In the philosophy of language, the distinction between concept and object is attributable to the German philosopher Gottlob Frege.
